  What you need to do (Phase 2 — dashboard)                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                   
  I'll give you a step-by-step. Total time: ~15-20 min.                                                                            
   
  A. Railway (~10 min)                                                                                                             
                                                            
  1. Sign in to railway.app → New Project → Deploy from GitHub repo → select this repo.                                            
  2. Once detected, Railway will probably try to deploy from root. Edit the service:
    - Settings → Root Directory: apps/api                                                                                          
    - Settings → Build: Dockerfile (Railway should auto-detect apps/api/Dockerfile)
    - Settings → Watch Paths: apps/api/** (so changes to web/mobile don't trigger API redeploys)                                   
  3. Create the staging environment: in the project, you'll see a default environment named production — rename to staging if      
  Railway lets you, or create a new one named staging. (We'll add production next.)                                                
  4. Add Postgres: in staging env → + New → Database → PostgreSQL.                                                                 
  5. Add env vars to staging: API service → Variables tab:                                                                         
    - DATABASE_URL = ${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}} (variable reference — Railway autocompletes)                                       
    - GIN_MODE = release                                                                                                           
    - (Don't set PORT — Railway sets it automatically.)                                                                            
  6. Wait for deploy → check the API service URL → curl https://<your-railway-url>/health should return {"status":"ok"}.           
  7. Repeat for production env: Settings → Environments → New Environment → name production. Add Postgres add-on to it. Set the    
  same vars (DATABASE_URL + GIN_MODE=release). For now, the production env can deploy from main too — you'll switch to manual      
  promotion later.                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                   
  B. Vercel (~5 min)                                                                                                               
   
  1. Sign in to vercel.com → Add New → Project → import the GitHub repo.                                                           
  2. Configure:                                             
    - Root Directory: apps/web                                                                                                     
    - Framework Preset: Vite (auto-detected)                
    - Include source files outside of the Root Directory: YES (toggle on — this is the monorepo install fix from Q5)               
    - Install Command: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile (override default if needed)                                                 
    - Build Command: leave default (pnpm build from apps/web)                                                                      
    - Output Directory: dist (Vite default)                                                                                        
  3. Add env var: Settings → Environment Variables → VITE_API_BASE_URL = your Railway staging URL (e.g.                            
  https://tend-api-staging-xxxx.up.railway.app). Apply to all three Vercel envs (Production / Preview / Development).              
  4. Deploy. Once green, hit the production URL; the SPA should load.                                                              
  5. Open a draft PR with any trivial change to apps/web/ — Vercel should comment a preview URL within ~2 min.                     
                                                                                                                                   
  C. Paste the URLs back                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                   
  Reply with:                                                                                                                      
  - Railway staging API URL: https://...                    
  - Railway production API URL: https://... (will be different if you spun up a separate prod env)                                 
  - Vercel production web URL: https://...                                                        
                                                                                                                                   
  I'll then:                                                
  1. Update README.md's "Deployments" table with the real URLs                                                                     
  2. Run AC verification (curl /health + /health/db against both staging and production)                                           
  3. Update story → review                                                                                                         
  4. You'll then run /bmad-code-review on Story 1.2                                                                                
                                                            
